Company Overview of Santander UK plc



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Santander UK plc provides a range of banking and financial products and services to personal, business, and public sector customers in the United Kingdom. The company operates through Retail Banking, Commercial Banking, and Global Corporate Banking segments. Its deposit products include interest-bearing and non-interest-bearing current and demand accounts, savings accounts, and time deposits. The company offers residential mortgage loans, personal loans, credit cards, consumer finance, business banking products, and overdrafts, as well as insurance policies. It also provides treasury, invoice discounting, cash transmission, trade finance, asset finance, and commercial real estate and social ...
Santander UK plc provides a range of banking and financial products and services to personal, business, and public sector customers in the United Kingdom. The company operates through Retail Banking, Commercial Banking, and Global Corporate Banking segments. Its deposit products include interest-bearing and non-interest-bearing current and demand accounts, savings accounts, and time deposits. The company offers residential mortgage loans, personal loans, credit cards, consumer finance, business banking products, and overdrafts, as well as insurance policies. It also provides treasury, invoice discounting, cash transmission, trade finance, asset finance, and commercial real estate and social housing loans; currency fluctuations management and interest rate risk protection products; and capital markets finance arrangements and specialist trade finance solutions. The company operates through a network of 841 branches and 67 corporate business centers, as well as through ATM, telephony, digital, mobile, Internet, and intermediary channels. Santander UK plc was incorporated in 1988 and is based in London, the United Kingdom. Santander UK plc is a subsidiary of Santander UK Group Holdings plc.
